.SH BUGS
Only knows about Unix pathnames. Thus, some AmigaDOS and all MS\-DOS
input filenames will yield unexpected results. This problem can be
circumvented by using the
.B {\-o,\-\-output}
option.
.PP
Beware of filenames that are too long for the appended `.tex' to fit.
It would be a shame if the
.I Pascal
source file was inadvertently overwritten by the
.I LaTeX
file.
